## What You Should Skip

| Thing | Why skip |
|-------|----------|
| Visible sandbox marker (`⚠️-sandbox-only`) | You were right — it doesn't help you, and it's not a meaningful security factor |
| `sudo -u llm-test` | Leaky, inherits environment weirdly, feels like isolation without delivering it |
| Docker as *primary* isolation | On macOS it runs inside a VM anyway — but Docker is still valuable as a **workflow + reproducibility layer**, not a security boundary |
| Chasing `sandbox-exec` replacements | Dead ecosystem, better alternatives exist |

---

## Final Mental Model

Don't ask: *"Is this safe?"*

Ask: *"Where do I want this to be allowed to fail?"*

| Failure domain | Recovery action |
|----------------|-----------------|
| Sandbox dir | `llm-nuke` |
| User account | Delete `/Users/llm-test` |
| VM | Delete VM file |

**If you can delete the boundary, you control the risk.**

